Aishwarya Rai Bachchan’s father hospitalised, actor visits with her husband 
9-3-2017 
Bollywood actor Aishwarya Rai Bachchan’s dad, Krishnaraj Rai, has been admitted to a city hospital where he was shifted to the ICU.

Abhishek Bachchan walks with his wife actress Aishwarya Rai Bachchan attend a prayer meeting for Veerappa Shetty, the father of actor Suniel Shetty in Mumbai on March 4. (AFP)

“Aishwarya’s father Krishnaraj Rai has been admitted to Lilavati Hospital in suburban Bandra,” Aishwarya’s publicist said. The publicist, however, did not share any further details.

Read more

An Indian Express report quoted a source as saying that Aishwarya’s dad is likely to be suffering from a recurrence of cancer. He was supposed to be discharged after a two-week stay in the hospital, but has now been shifted to the ICU, it added.

Aishwarya and her actor husband Abhishek Bachchan visited him in the hospital Wednesday night.

Read more

Meanwhile, on the work front, speculations are rife that the couple will reportedly be seen together after a gap of seven years in a film titled Gulab Jamun, to be backed by Phantom Films.

